{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/william-petty-2nd-earl-of-shelburne","content_id":"ed3fa821-b07e-46fa-a0c7-1164f472c070","description":"“The sun of Great Britain will set whenever she acknowledges the independence of America – the independence of America would end in the ruin of England.”","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Earl of Shelburne was unfairly branded ‘the Jesuit of Berkeley Square’ on account of his reputation as a dissembler. His reformist inclinations, political independence and vituperative speeches certainly made him a difficult colleague, with more appeal to posterity than to his contemporary politicians.</p>\n\n<p>Read more about William Petty, 2nd Earl of Shelburne on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://history.blog.gov.uk/2015/08/26/william-petty-2nd-earl-of-shelburne-whig-1782-1783/\" class=\"govuk-link\">History of government blog.</a></p>\n</div>","born":"2 May 1737, Dublin, Ireland","dates_in_office":[{"end_year":1783,"start_year":1782}],"died":"7 May 1805, London","interesting_facts":"In power at the time of the treaty of Paris which ended the American Revolutionary War/American War of Independence. ","major_acts":"","political_party":"Whig"},"document_type":"historic_appointment","first_published_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:34+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/william-petty-2nd-earl-of-shelburne","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/william-petty-2nd-earl-of-shelburne","base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/william-petty-2nd-earl-of-shelburne","content_id":"ed3fa821-b07e-46fa-a0c7-1164f472c070","document_type":"historic_appointment","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:34Z","schema_name":"historic_appointment","title":"William Petty, 2nd Earl of Shelburne","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/history/past-prime-minist